<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;border-bottom:Solid 0.75pt;padding-bottom:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-right:86.11%;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1)</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;">Member of Audit Committee.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2)</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;">Member of Compensation Committee.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(3)</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;">Member of Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(4)</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;">Lead Independent Director.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(5)</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Mr. Jurvetson has been on a leave of absence from the Board since November 2017.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Elon Musk<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> has served as our Chief Executive Officer since October 2008 and as Chairman of our Board since April 2004. Mr.&#160;Musk has also served as Chief Executive Officer, Chief Technology Officer and Chairman of Space Exploration Technologies Corporation, a company which is developing and launching advanced rockets for satellite, and eventually human, transportation (&#8220;</font><font style="text-decoration:underline;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">SpaceX</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">&#8221;), since May 2002, and served as Chairman of the Board of SolarCity Corporation, a solar installation company (&#8220;</font><font style="text-decoration:underline;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">SolarCity</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">&#8221;), from July 2006 until its acquisition by us in November 2016. Mr.&#160;Musk is also a founder of The Boring Company, an infrastructure company, and Neuralink Corp, a company focused on developing brain-machine interfaces. Prior to SpaceX, Mr.&#160;Musk co-founded PayPal, an electronic payment system, which was acquired by eBay in October 2002, and Zip2 Corporation, a provider of Internet enterprise software and services, which was acquired by Compaq in March 1999. Mr.&#160;Musk holds a B.A. in physics from the University of Pennsylvania and a B.S. in business from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that Mr.&#160;Musk possesses specific attributes that qualify him to serve as a member of our Board, including the perspective and experience he brings as our Chief Executive Officer, one of our founders and our largest stockholder, which brings historic knowledge, operational expertise and continuity to our Board.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Brad Buss<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> has been a member of our Board since November 2009. From August 2014 until his retirement in February 2016, Mr.&#160;Buss served as the Chief Financial Officer of SolarCity. Prior to joining SolarCity, from August 2005 to June 2014, Mr.&#160;Buss was the Executive Vice President of Finance and Administration and Chief Financial Officer of Cypress Semiconductor Corporation, a semiconductor design and manufacturing company. Mr.&#160;Buss served as Vice President of Finance at Altera Corp., a semiconductor design and manufacturing company, from March 2000 to March 2001 and from October 2001 to August 2005. From March 2001 to October 2001, Mr.&#160;Buss served as the Chief Financial Officer of Zaffire, Inc., a developer and manufacturer of optical networking equipment. Mr.&#160;Buss also serves as a director of Advance Auto Parts, Inc. and Cavium, Inc., and also served as a director of CafePress Inc. from October 2007 until July 2016. Mr.&#160;Buss holds a B.A. in economics from McMaster University and an honors business administration degree, majoring in finance and accounting, from the University of Windsor.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that Mr.&#160;Buss possesses specific attributes that qualify him to serve as a member of our Board, including his executive experience and his financial and accounting expertise with both public and private companies in diverse industries.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">9</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU12"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Robyn Denholm</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> has been a member of our Board since August 2014. Since January 2017, Ms.&#160;Denholm has been Chief Operations Officer of Telstra Corporation Limited, a telecommunications company. Prior to Telstra, from August 2</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">007 to February 2016, Ms.&#160;Denholm was with Juniper Networks, Inc., a manufacturer of networking equipment, serving first as its Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer and then as its Executive Vice President and Chief Financial and Operations</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> Officer. Prior to joining Juniper Networks, Ms.&#160;Denholm served in various executive roles at Sun Microsystems, Inc. from January 1996 to August 2007. Ms.&#160;Denholm also served at Toyota Motor Corporation Australia for seven years and at Arthur Andersen&#160;&amp; Co</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">mpany for five years in various finance assignments. Ms.&#160;Denholm previously served as a director of ABB Ltd., an automation technology company, from 2016 to 2017 and of Echelon Corporation Inc. from 2008 to 2013. Ms.&#160;Denholm is a Fellow of the Institute of</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> Chartered Accountants of Australia and holds a Bachelor&#8217;s degree in Economics from the University of Sydney and a Master&#8217;s degree in Commerce from the University of New South Wales.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that Ms.&#160;Denholm possesses specific attributes that qualify her to serve as a member of our Board and chair of our Audit Committee, including her executive experience and her financial and accounting expertise with international companies, including in the technology and automotive industries.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Ira Ehrenpreis<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> has been a member of our Board since May 2007. Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis has been a venture capitalist since 1996 when he joined Technology Partners, where he is a partner and has led its Cleantech practice for several years as a managing member. Since 2015, Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis has also been a managing partner of the venture capital firm of DBL Partners. In the venture capital community, he has served on the board of the National Venture Capital Association and currently serves as the President of the Western Association of Venture Capitalists and the Chairman of the VCNetwork, an organization comprising more than 1,000 venture capitalists. In the Cleantech sector, he has served on several industry boards, including the American Council on Renewable Energy and the Cleantech Venture Network (Past Chairman of Advisory Board), and was the Chairman of the Clean-Tech Investor Summit in 2005, 2006, 2007, 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011, 2012 and 2013. Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis serves as Chairman of the World Energy Innovation Forum. Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis holds a B.A. from the University of California, Los Angeles and a J.D. and M.B.A. from Stanford University.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis possesses specific attributes that qualify him to serve as a member of our Board and to serve as chair of our Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and chair of our Compensation Committee, including his experience in the Cleantech and venture capital industries.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Antonio Gracias<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> has been a member of our Board since May 2007 and has served as our Lead Independent Director since September 2010. Since 2003, Mr.&#160;Gracias has been Chief Executive Officer of Valor Management Corp., a private equity firm. Mr.&#160;Gracias is a director of SpaceX, and was a director of SolarCity until its acquisition by us in November 2016. Mr.&#160;Gracias holds a joint B.S. and M.S. degree in international finance and economics from the Georgetown University School of Foreign Service and a J.D. from the University of Chicago Law School.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that Mr.&#160;Gracias possesses specific attributes that qualify him to serve as a member of our Board, including his management experience with a nationally recognized private equity firm and his operations management and supply chain optimization expertise.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Stephen Jurvetson<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> has been a member of our Board since June 2009. Mr. Jurvetson has been on a leave of absence from the Board since November 2017. Mr.&#160;Jurvetson was a Managing Director of Draper Fisher Jurvetson, a venture capital firm, from 1995 to 2017. Mr.&#160;Jurvetson is a director of SpaceX, from which he is also on a leave of absence. Mr.&#160;Jurvetson holds B.S. and M.S. degrees in electrical engineering from Stanford University and an M.B.A. from the Stanford Business School.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that Mr.&#160;Jurvetson possesses specific attributes that qualify him to serve as a member of our Board, including his experience in the venture capital industry and his years of business and leadership experience.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU13"></a>James Murdoch<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> has been a member of our Board since July 2017. Mr. Murdoch has held a number of leadership roles at Twenty-First Century Fox, Inc. (&#8220;</font><font style="text-decoration:underline;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">21CF</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">&#8221;) over two decades, including as its CEO since 2015, its Co-Chief Operating Officer from 2014 to 2015, its Deputy Chief Operating Officer and Chairman and CEO, International from 2011 to 2014 and its Chairman and Chief Executive, Europe and Asia from 2007 to 2011. Previously, he served as the CEO of Sky plc from 2003 to 2007, and as the Chairman and CEO of STAR Group </font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">10</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">Li</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">mited, a subsidiary of 21CF, from 2000 to 2003. Mr. Murdoch also serves on the boards of 21CF, Sky plc, where he has served as Chairman since 2016, and New Corp, and formerly served on the boards of GlaxoSmithKline plc from 2009 to 2012 and of Sotheby&#8217;s fr</font><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;">om 2010 to 2012.&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that Mr. Murdoch possesses specific attributes that qualify him to serve as a member of our Board, including his lengthy executive and board experience across numerous companies, extensive knowledge of international markets and strategies, and experience with the adoption of new technologies.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Kimbal Musk<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> has been a member of our Board since April 2004. Mr.&#160;Musk is a co-founder of The Kitchen, a growing family of businesses with the goal of providing all Americans with access to real food, and has also served as its CEO since its founding in 2004. In 2010, Mr. Musk became the Executive Director of The Kitchen Community, a non-profit organization that creates learning gardens in schools across the United States. Mr. Musk also co-founded Square Roots, an urban farming incubator program, in 2016. Previously, Mr. Musk was a co-founder of Zip2 Corporation, a provider of enterprise software and services, which was acquired by Compaq in March 1999. From 2012 to 2015, Mr. Musk was a director of the Anschutz Health and Wellness Center, a facility at the University of Colorado School of Medicine providing research, education and wellness services with the goal of achieving healthier lifestyles. Mr.&#160;Musk is also a director of SpaceX and of Chipotle Mexican Grill, Inc., an international chain of Mexican-themed restaurants. Mr.&#160;Musk holds a B. Comm. in business from Queen&#8217;s University and is a graduate of The French Culinary Institute in New York City. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that Mr.&#160;Musk possesses specific attributes that qualify him to serve as a member of our Board, including his business experience in retail and consumer markets, his lengthy experience on our Board, and his experience with technology companies.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Linda Johnson Rice<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;"> has been a member of our Board since July 2017. Ms. Rice is currently the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Johnson Publishing Company, which owns Fashion Fair Cosmetics as well as extensive published works, where she has served in one or both capacities continuously since 1988 after joining in 1980. Ms. Rice has also served as Chief Executive Officer of EBONY Media Operations, which publishes EBONY and Jet magazines, since March 2017, and is a director and Chairman Emeritus of EBONY Media Holdings, its parent company. Ms. Rice also serves on the boards of the Omnicom Group and GrubHub Inc. Ms. Rice is Trustee at the Art Institute of Chicago, President of the Chicago Public Library Board of Directors, Council Member of The Smithsonian&#8217;s National Museum of African American History and Culture, and board member of After School Matters and Northwestern Memorial Corporation. Ms. Rice holds a B.A. in Journalism from the University of Southern California&#8217;s Annenberg School of Communication and an M.B.A. from Northwestern University&#8217;s Kellogg School of Management. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We believe that Ms. Rice possesses specific attributes that qualify her to serve as a member of our Board, including her extensive corporate management and board experience and her understanding of consumer businesses.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">See &#8220;<font style="font-style:italic;">Corporate Governance</font>&#8221; and &#8220;<font style="font-style:italic;">Executive Compensation&#8212;Compensation of Directors</font>&#8221; below for additional information regarding the Board.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">11</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU14"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_TWO"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_THREE"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_TWO"></a>PROPOSA</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_THREE"></a>L</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> TWO</font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">RATIFICATION OF APPOINTMENT OF</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="GENERAL1"></a><a name="GENERAL1"></a>General</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Audit Committee has selected PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as Tesla&#8217;s independent registered public accounting firm to audit the consolidated financial statements of Tesla for the fiscal year ending December&#160;31, 2018, which will include an audit of the effectiveness of Tesla&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting. PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP has audited Tesla&#8217;s financial statements since 2005. A representative of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP is expected to be present at the meeting, will have the opportunity to make a statement if he or she desires to do so, and is expected to be available to respond to appropriate questions.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Stockholder ratification of the selection of our independent registered public accounting firm is a matter of good corporate practice. In the event that this selection is not ratified by the affirmative vote of a majority of the shares present and voting at the meeting in person or by proxy, the appointment of the independent registered public accounting firm will be reconsidered by the Audit Committee. Even if the selection is ratified, the Audit Committee in its discretion may direct the appointment of a different accounting firm at any time during the year if the Audit Committee determines that such a change would be in the best interests of Tesla and its stockholders.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PRINCIPAL_ACCOUNTING_FEES_SERVICES"></a><a name="PRINCIPAL_ACCOUNTING_FEES_SERVICES"></a>Principal Accounting Fees and Services</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The following table presents fees billed for professional audit services and other services rendered to Tesla by PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP for the years ended December&#160;31, 2016 and 2017. The dollar amounts in the table and accompanying footnotes are in thousands.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#CFF0FC" style="width:1%;">

<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#CFF0FC" style="width:10%;">

<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#CFF0FC" style="width:1%;">

<td valign="bottom"  style="width:10%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #000000;">

<td valign="bottom"  style="width:1%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt transparent;">

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;border-bottom:Solid 0.75pt;padding-bottom:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-right:86.11%;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1)</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;">Audit Fees consist of fees billed for professional services rendered for the audit of Tesla&#8217;s consolidated financial statements included in Tesla&#8217;s Annual Report on Form 10-K and for the review of the financial statements included in Tesla&#8217;s Quarterly Reports on Form 10-Q, as well as services that generally only Tesla&#8217;s independent registered public accounting firm can reasonably provide, including statutory audits and services rendered in connection with SEC filings. The Audit Fees incurred in 2016 also include fees of $3,332 related to services performed in connection with Tesla&#8217;s acquisition of SolarCity and its securities offerings, and the Audit Fees incurred in 2017 also include fees of $403 relating to services performed in connection with Tesla&#8217;s securities offerings, in each case including comfort letters, consents and review of documents filed with the SEC and other offering documents.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2)</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;">Audit-Related Fees consists of fees billed for professional services for assistance with interpretation of accounting standards.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(3)</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Tax Fees in 2016 consisted primarily of $31 related to consultation and assistance for employment tax-related matters, and Tax Fees in 2017 consisted primarily of $64 related to consultation and assistance for foreign taxation matters.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(4)</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;">Other Fees consist of an annual license fee of $2 in 2016 and 2017 for use of accounting research software.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">12</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU15"></a><a name="PREAPPROVAL_AUDIT_NONAUDIT_SERVICES"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PREAPPROVAL_AUDIT_NONAUDIT_SERVICES"></a>Pre-Approval of Audit </font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">and Non-Audit Services</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla&#8217;s Audit Committee has adopted a policy for pre-approving audit and non-audit services and associated fees of Tesla&#8217;s independent registered public accounting firm. Under this policy, the Audit Committee must pre- approve all services and associated fees provided to Tesla by its independent registered public accounting firm, with certain <font style="font-style:italic;">de minimis</font> exceptions described in the policy.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">All PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP services and fees in fiscal 2016 and 2017 were pre-approved by the Audit Committee.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board Recommends a Vote<font style="font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-style:italic;">FOR</font><font style="font-weight:normal;"> </font>the Ratification of the Appointment of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as Tesla&#8217; s Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm For the Fiscal Year Ending December 31,&#160;2018.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><br /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">13</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU16"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_THREE1"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_THREE1"></a>PROPOSA</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">L THREE</font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL TO REQUIRE THAT THE CHAIR OF THE <br />BOARD OF DIRECTORS BE AN INDEPENDENT DIRECTOR</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In accordance with SEC rules, we have set forth below a stockholder proposal from Mr. Jing Zhao, along with a supporting statement of the proponent, exactly as submitted by Mr. Zhao. Mr. Zhao has notified us that he is the beneficial owner of twelve (12) shares of the Company&#8217;s common stock and intends to present the following proposal at the 2018 Annual Meeting. Mr. Zhao&#8217;s address is 1745 Cooperleaf Ct., Concord, CA 94519. The stockholder proposal will be required to be voted upon at the 2018 Annual Meeting only if properly presented.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEMEN"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEMEN"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">*<font style="margin-left:36pt;">**</font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="SHAREHOLDER_PROPOSAL_ON_BOARD_CHAIRMAN_I"></a><a name="SHAREHOLDER_PROPOSAL_ON_BOARD_CHAIRMAN_I"></a>Shareholder Proposal on Board Chairman Independence</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Resolved: shareholders recommend that Tesla adopt a policy that the chairman of our board of directors be an independent director. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="SUPPORTING_STATEMENT"></a><a name="SUPPORTING_STATEMENT"></a>Supporting Statement</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mr. Elon Musk has served as Chief Executive Officer for ten years since 2008 and as Chairman of the Board of Directors for fourteen years since 2004. Although the current leadership structure, in which the positions of Chairman and CEO are held by one person, could provide an effective leadership for Tesla at the early stage, now in this much more highly competitive and rapidly changing technology industry, it is more and more difficult to oversee Tesla's business and senior management (especially to minimize any potential conflicts) that may result from combining the positions of CEO and Chairman. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">For example, in November 2016 Tesla completed acquisition of SolarCity, so Tesla's CEO and Chairman is also a significant stockholder of SolarCity and Chairman of its Board of Directors; Jeffrey B. Straubel, Tesla's Chief Technical Officer, is also a member of SolarCity's Board of Directors; and certain other members of Tesla's Board of Directors have interests in SolarCity (NOTICE OF 2017 ANNUAL MEETING OF STOCKHOLDERS p.46.). Elon Musk is also the CEO, Chief Technical Officer and a significant stockholder of SpaceX. Kimbal Musk, a member of Tesla's Board of Directors, is also a member of the board of directors of SpaceX. In addition, certain other members of Tesla's Board of Directors have interests in SpaceX ...... (NOTICE OF 2017 ANNUAL MEETING OF STOCKHOLDERS p.47.). </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">An independent chairman of the board of directors is the prevailing practice in the international market, such as in the United Kingdom. In the United States too, many big companies already have or began to have an independent Board Chairman. Tesla should not be exception. </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">*<font style="margin-left:36pt;">**</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD"></a>Opposing Statement of the Board</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board believes that the Company&#8217;s success to date would not have been possible if the Board was led by another director lacking Elon Musk&#8217;s day-to-day exposure to the Company&#8217;s business. In light of the significant future opportunities for growth and the careful execution needed in order for the Company to achieve it, the Board believes that the Company is still best served by Mr. Musk continuing to serve as Chairman.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU17"></a>Moreover, the role of the Lead Independent Director protects the Company against any potential governance issues arising from a non-independent director serving as Chairman. This position is vested with broad authority to lead the actions of the independent directors and communicate regularly with the Chief Executive Officer. Additionally, the Company now has seven independent directors following the addition of two additional </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">14</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">independent directors in July 2017. The Board believes that the broad authority of the Lead Independen</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">t Director and the presence of six other independent directors ensures that the Board acts independently. This current Board structure also is consistent with majority practice at large public companies: according to the 2017 Spencer Stuart Board Index, 72</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">% of companies in the S&amp;P 500 do not have an independent board chairman.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The proponent acknowledges that a combined Chief Executive Officer and Chairman is an effective form of leadership for an early-stage company, until it faces increased competition and rapid technological changes. The Board believes that it is precisely during times when a company must quickly adapt to constant change and outside pressures that Board leadership needs to be lockstep with the Company&#8217;s operations. Our achievements to date notwithstanding, the Company is still at a point in its development where we must execute well in order to realize our long-term goals, and separating the roles of Chief Executive Officer and Chairman at this time would not serve the best interests of the Company or its stockholders.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board Recommends a Vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the Stockholder Proposal to Require That the Chair of the Board of Directors be an Independent Director.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><br /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">15</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU18"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_FOUR"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_FOUR"></a>PROPOSA</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">L FOUR </font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING PROXY ACCESS </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In accordance with SEC rules, we have set forth below a stockholder proposal from James McRitchie, along with a supporting statement of the proponent, exactly as submitted by Mr. McRitchie. Mr. McRitchie has notified us that he is the beneficial owner of 130 shares of the Company&#8217;s common stock and intends to present the following proposal at the 2018 Annual Meeting through his designee, John Chevedden. Mr. McRitchie&#8217;s address is 9295 Yorkship Court, Elk Grove, CA 95758. The stockholder proposal will be required to be voted upon at the 2018 Annual Meeting only if properly presented.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">*<font style="margin-left:36pt;">**</font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Proposal 4 - Shareholder Proxy Access</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">RESOLVED: Shareholders of Tesla Motors (&#8220;Tesla&#8221; or the &#8220;Company&#8221;) ask the board of directors (the &#8220;Board&#8221;) to amend its bylaws or other documents, as necessary, to provide proxy access for shareholders as follows:</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><a name="_Ref511983106"></a>Nominating shareholders or shareholder groups (&#8220;Nominators&#8221;) must beneficially own 3% or more of the Company's outstanding common stock (&#8220;Required Stock&#8221;) continuously for at least three years and pledge to hold such stock through the annual meeting.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Nominators may submit a statement not exceeding 500 words in support of each nominee to be included in the Company proxy.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">3.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The number of shareholder-nominated candidates eligible to appear in proxy materials shall be one quarter of the directors then serving or two, whichever is greater.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">4.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">No limitation shall be placed on the number of shareholders that can aggregate their shares to achieve the 3% of Required Stock.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">5.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">No limitation shall be placed on the re-nomination of shareholder nominees by Nominators based on the number or percentage of votes received in any election.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">6.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Company shall not require that Nominators pledge to hold stock after the annual meeting if their nominees fail to win election.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">7.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-style:italic;">Loaned securities shall be counted as belonging to a nominating shareholder if the shareholder represents it has the legal right to recall those securities for voting purposes and will hold those securities through the date of the annual meeting.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Supporting Statement: The SEC's universal proxy access Rule 14a-11 (https://www.sec.gov/rules/final/2010/33-9136.pdf) was vacated after a court decision regarding the SEC's cost-benefit analysis. Therefore, proxy access rights must be established on a company-by- company basis. Subsequently, <font style="font-style:italic;">Proxy Access in the United States: Revisiting the Proposed SEC Rule</font> (http://www.cfapubs.org/doi/pdf/10.2469/ccb.v2014.n9.1) a cost-benefit analysis by CFA Institute, found proxy access would &#8220;benefit both the markets and corporate boardrooms, with little cost or disruption,&#8221; raising US market capitalization by up to $140.3 billion. <font style="font-style:italic;">Public Versus Private Provision of Governance: The Case of Proxy Access</font> (http://ssrn.com/abstract=2635695) found a 0.5 percent average increase in shareholder value for proxy access targeted firms. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Proxy Access: Best Practices 2017 </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(http://www.cii.org/files/publications/misc/Proxy_Access_2017_FINAL.pdf) by CII, notes that &#8220;while proxy access has gained broad acceptance, some adopting companies have included, or are considering including, provisions that could significantly impair shareholders' ability to use it.&#8221; The report &#8220;highlights the best practices CII recommends for implementing proxy access.&#8221;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">16</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU19"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Adoption of bylaws with </font><font style="font-style:italic;">all</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> the requested elements outlined above would help ensure meaningful proxy assess[sic] is available to shareholders. Similar proposals won an average of 82.5% For, 14.3% Against, and 0.8% Abstain from July 16, 2016 to June 30, 2017, according to Proxy Insig</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ht. </font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Increase Shareholder Value</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Vote for Shareholder Proxy Access - Proposal 4</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">*<font style="margin-left:36pt;">**</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT"></a>Opposing Statement of the Board</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">This proposal would not serve the best interests of the Company or its stockholders, for the reasons stated below.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">First, the Company already has mechanisms to promote the accountability of the Board to its stockholders. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee of the Board is comprised entirely of independent directors. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee regularly reviews the composition, size and performance of the Board and its committees, evaluates individual Board members, and identifies and evaluates candidates for election or re-election to the Board. The Company has also implemented means for stockholders to recommend director candidates for the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee&#8217;s consideration, nominate candidates at stockholder meetings, and contact the Board directly.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Second, through the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee&#8217;s efforts, the Board has steadily added independent directors to the Board. Robyn Denholm was appointed to the Board in 2014 and Linda Johnson Rice and James Murdoch were appointed in 2017. In addition to being independent, each of these individuals is highly experienced as a senior executive and board member at multiple well-established companies.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Third, the version of proxy access formulated by the proponent may create an opportunity for special interests that seek only short-term returns rather than having the Company&#8217;s long-term interests in mind. This is particularly harmful for a company like ours, which is still in an early stage of development and undergoing rapid growth. Like other fast-growing technology companies, we may experience significant short-term swings in the price of our stock that are unrelated to our long-term prospects, and the proposal would allow special interests seeking only short-term returns&#8212;or even our competitors&#8212;to take advantage of such swings to disrupt the focus of the Company.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Notably, the proposal provides no safeguards against stockholders seeking to use proxy access to nominate directors who will act only in their individual interests. In fact, the proposal would not ensure that the stockholders seeking proxy access be truly invested in the Company even on a short-term basis, as it would be available to individuals who have relinquished voting and investment power over their shares and hold a net short position. Indeed, this proposal could be exploited by corporate raiders solely to effect a change of control, which should not be the purpose or outcome of any proxy access provision.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board recognizes that proxy access is a topic of growing interest in the investor community, and will continue to monitor and consider this topic. At this time, however, the Board believes that the process for director nomination and stockholder communication that we have already implemented is the right approach to provide a voice to our stockholders while promoting their long-term returns and the Company&#8217;s ultimate success.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board Recommends a Vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the Stockholder Proposal Regarding Proxy Access.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">17</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU20"></a><a name="CORPORATE_GOVERNANCE"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="CORPORATE_GOVERNANCE"></a>CORPORATE </font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">GOVERNANCE</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="INVESTOR_OUTREACH"></a><a name="INVESTOR_OUTREACH"></a>Investor Outreach</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">During 2014, the Board determined to formally identify, approach and establish an active dialogue with our largest stockholders and conduct an extensive review of our corporate governance practices. We inaugurated a program of periodic investor outreach to ensure that Tesla&#8217;s Board and management understand and consider the issues that matter most to our stockholders. We have gradually expanded this program over time to include senior members of management and the Board, who have participated in hosting extended series of meetings with and preparing presentations to a broad base of investors. For example, in 2017, such meetings were held with many of our largest institutional investors to obtain investor feedback and present on a variety of corporate governance issues, including the role and number of independent directors on the Board. Through this program, we have received and continue to periodically receive helpful input regarding a number of stockholder-related matters, and have adopted a number of significant changes to our corporate governance practices in addition to welcoming two new independent directors to our Board in 2017, bringing the total number of independent directors to seven of nine members.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Moreover, members of our Board and management have proactively sought input from our investors when considering important corporate actions that involve matters of corporate governance and alignment with stockholder interests. For example,<font style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;color:#000000;"> at the request of the Compensation Committee, Ira Ehrenpreis and our General Counsel, Todd Maron, had calls in 2017 with 15 of our largest institutional stockholders to discuss and solicit their views regarding Elon Musk&#8217;s compensation arrangements. As the Board thereafter deliberated for several months on a new performance award for Mr. Musk, it gave great weight to the feedback that our stockholders provided during these early calls, and it incorporated much of that feedback into the ultimate design of the award, culminating in the </font>grant of a performance-based stock option award to Mr. Musk in January 2018 (the &#8220;<font style="text-decoration:underline;">2018 CEO Performance Award</font>&#8221;)<font style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;color:#000000;"> that was subsequently approved by approximately 73% of the votes cast by stockholders (other than Mr. Musk or Kimbal Musk) at a meeting to approve such award.</font> </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We do not expect that we will always be able to address all of our stockholders&#8217; feedback. However, we seek to optimize our corporate governance by continually refining our relevant policies, procedures and practices to align the needs of the Company with evolving regulations and best practices, issues raised by our stockholders, and other factors as circumstances warrant.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="CODE_BUSINESS_CONDUCT_ETHICS_CORPORATE_G"></a><a name="CODE_BUSINESS_CONDUCT_ETHICS_CORPORATE_G"></a>Code of Business Conduct and Ethics and Corporate Governance Guidelines</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board sets high standards for Tesla&#8217;s employees, officers and directors. Tesla is committed to establishing an operating framework that exercises appropriate oversight of responsibilities at all levels throughout the company and managing its affairs consistent with high principles of business ethics. Accordingly, Tesla has adopted a Code of Business Conduct and Ethics, which is applicable to Tesla and its subsidiaries&#8217; directors, officers and employees. Tesla has also adopted Corporate Governance Guidelines, which, in conjunction with our certificate of incorporation, bylaws, and charters of the standing committees of our Board, form the framework for Tesla&#8217;s corporate governance. The Code of Business Conduct and Ethics and the Corporate Governance Guidelines are each available on Tesla&#8217;s website at: http://ir.tesla.com/corporate-governance.cfm. Tesla will disclose on its website any amendment to the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics, as well as any waivers of the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics, that are required to be disclosed by the rules of the SEC or The NASDAQ Stock Market LLC (&#8220;<font style="text-decoration:underline;">NASDAQ</font>&#8221;).</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="DIRECTOR_INDEPENDENCE"></a><a name="DIRECTOR_INDEPENDENCE"></a>Director Independence</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board has determined that, with the exception of Elon Musk and Kimbal Musk, all of its current members are &#8220;independent directors&#8221; as that term is defined in the listing standards of NASDAQ.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU21"></a>Other than Elon Musk, no current director is or has ever been an employee of Tesla. In the course of determining the independence of each non-employee director, the Board considers the annual amount of Tesla&#8217;s sales to, or purchases from, any company where a non-employee director serves as an executive officer. In order to find that a director is independent, the Board must determine that any such sales or purchases were made in the </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">18</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ordinary course of business and the</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> amount of such sales or purchases in each of the past three fiscal years was less than 5% of Tesla&#8217;s or the applicable company&#8217;s consolidated gross revenues for the applicable year. The Board undertook an analysis for each non-employee director and consid</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ered all other relevant facts and circumstances, including the director&#8217;s commercial, accounting, legal, banking, consulting, charitable and familial relationships. The Board specifically reviewed the transactions specified below in &#8220;</font><font style="font-style:italic;">Certain Relationships </font><font style="font-style:italic;">and Related Party Transactions&#8212;Related Party Transactions</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8221; and the additional considerations described immediately below to the extent they were identified with respect to any of the non-employee directors.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:5.24%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">With respect to Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis, the following were among the relevant considerations:</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.84%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;">Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis is a manager of DBL Partners Fund III (&#8220;</font><font style="text-decoration:underline;font-family:Times New Roman;">DBL III</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;">&#8221;). Each of Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis and DBL III is a minority investor in SpaceX. Tesla and certain Tesla directors have relationships with SpaceX as set forth in this section and below in &#8220;</font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Times New Roman;">Certain Relationships and Related Party Transactions&#8212;Related Party Transactions&#8212;SpaceX.</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;">&#8221;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>

<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;">Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis is a co-owner of DBL Partners. Another co-owner of DBL Partners is a manager of DBL Investors, which is also an investor in SpaceX. Mr.&#160;Ehrenpreis has no direct or indirect investment control or pecuniary interest in DBL Investors.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.84%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.24%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;">Mr. Ehrenpreis serves a member of the board of directors of Mapbox Inc., a provider of custom online maps (&#8220;</font><font style="text-decoration:underline;font-family:Times New Roman;">Mapbox</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;">&#8221;).
